tab "ROE/Defend" {
    A uniformed force group's response to being attacked is determined
    by its Defending ROE.  The choice of ROE affects the number of
    casualties to both the attacking group and civilian bystanders.<p>

    The browser controls are described <<seebelow controls>>; the data
    fields are as follows:<p>

    <<topiclist Column Description>>

    <<topic "Nbhood">>The neighborhood in which the uniformed group
    will be defending.
    <</topic>>

    <<topic "Group">>The name of the defending uniformed group<</topic>>
    
    <<topic "ROE">>The ROE proper.<p>

    If the ROE is <b>HOLD_FIRE</b> then
    the group will never fire back at an attacker; no casualties will
    be inflicted upon the attack, and there will be no civilian
    collateral damage.<p>

    If the ROE is <b>FIRE_BACK_IF_PRESSED</b>, the group will fire
    back only if the attacker stands and fights.  In that case the
    attacker will take casualties, and there will be civilian
    collateral damage.<p>

