# Reports

tab "Reports" {
    The Reports tab displays all of the 
    <<cref reports reports>> produced by Athena.
    Some reports are produced automatically as Athena runs, but most
    are requested by the user via the <<menuref Reports>>.  Reports
    can also be 
    <<menuref "Reports/Save Hot List to Disk..." "saved to disk">>
    in text format.<p>

    The report browser contains the following elements:<p>

    <ul>
    <li> At the top, a tool bar containing the 
         <<seebelow controls "browser controls">>.
    <li> At the left, the <<seebelow bintree "bin tree">>.  The
         browser automatically sorts reports into bins by report type.
    <li> Below the tool bar, the 
         <<seebelow replist "report list">>, which lists the times and
         titles of the reports in the current bin.
    <li> Below the report list, the text of the currently selected
         report.
    </ul><p>

    <b><a name="controls">Browser Controls:</a></b>  The browser's
    toolbar contains the following controls:<p>

    <<topiclist Control Description>>

    <<topic {<img src="filterbox">}>>
    The filter box filters the reports displayed in the 
    <<seebelow replist "report list">> based on whether the reports
    contain the filter text or not.  Click on the sieve icon to pull
    down the filter menu; there are two choices:<p>

    <ul>
    <li> <b>Search Title and Text</b>
    <li> <b>Search Titles Only</b>
    </ul><p>

    Note that the report browser's filter box differs from the
    standard <<term filterbox>> used by most of the other browsers.
    <</topic>>

    <<topic {<img src="button_clock"}>>
    <b>Show Recent.</b>  Toggle this button to show only the most
    recent reports; untoggle 
    it to show all of the reports in the bin.
    <</topic>>

    <<topic {<img src="button_autoscroll"}>>
    <b>Auto-Scroll</b>.  Normally, the report browser automatically
    jumps to the latest 
    report in the current bin as new reports come in.  Toggle this
    button to prevent the browser from jumping away from the current
    report; untoggle it to restore the usual behavior.
    <</topic>>

    <<topic {<img src="control_hotlist"}>>
    Check the box to add the currently displayed report to the
    <<seebelow hotlist "Hot List">>.
    <</topic>>

    <</topiclist>>

    <b><a name="bintree">Bin Tree:</a></b>  Athena automatically sorts
    all reports into bins by type, so that it is easier to find a
    particular report later on.  Note that a report can appear in
    multiple bins. There are three special bins.<p>

    The <b>All Reports</b> bin contains all reports of every type.<p>

    The <b>Requested</b> bin 
    contains all reports requested by the user; whenever the user
    requests a report, the browser automatically switches to this
    bin.<p>

    <b><a name="replist">The Report List:</a></b> This pane lists the
    report ID number, <<term zulu>> and title of each report in the
    current bin.  Click on a report title to display it in the
    browser; double-click it to pop up a separate report viewer
    window.<p>

    The <b>Hot List</b> contains all reports the user has added to the 
    <<seebelow hotlist "Hot List">>.<p>

    <b><a name="hotlist">The Hot List:</a></b> The user can add
    reports of particular interest to the Hot List by checking the
    Hot List box that appears just above the text of the report.
    These reports then appear in the <b>Hot List</b> bin.  The reports
    in the Hot List can be 
    <<menuref "Reports/Save Hot List to Disk..." "saved to disk">>
    as a text file.<p>
}


